{
  "sectionNumber": "6.4.3",
  "title": "Disaster Preparedness",
  "type": "multi-block",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "paragraphs",
      "content": [
        "Due to geographical complexities, Nepal is located in a high-risk zone for natural disasters. Every year, significant loss of life and property occurs due to natural calamities. The trauma of the 2015 earthquake is still fresh. The sub-metropolitan city is also in a sensitive state regarding natural disasters, facing threats like flooding, erosion, pandemics, frost, hailstorms, earthquakes, fires, strong winds, and cold or heat waves. While these disasters generally cannot be fully controlled, their impact can be reduced by adopting mitigation measures.",
        "With the core motto of **\"Emergency Service, Volunteering in the Community,\"** the sub-metropolitan city has adopted policies to produce and mobilize trained volunteers at the ward and community levels, launch the **\"Green City, Nepalgunj's Ambition\"** campaign for environmental adaptation, purchase and store necessary rescue and relief materials, and give high priority to the protection and safety of vulnerable groups like senior citizens, persons with disabilities, children, and pregnant or postpartum women. It also aims to mainstream disaster management through legislation, continue residential insurance programs, and develop Nepalgunj as a disaster management hub for the western region."
      ]
    },
